Contrary to many students' opinions, I liked Prof. Lee's lectures and teaching style. At some times her accent hindered some understanding, but she was very sweet and always kept the lectures lighthearted with her enthusiasm and jokes. The midterm and final were straightforward; however, some of the assignments and labs were confusing at times.

She's a nice lady but the lectures were really difficult to understand. Luckily every concept in this class is easily learned on Youtube so I didn't mind. Assignments are easy and the midterm and final were fair, reflecting the content we learned in the course. Labs were useless and also didn't count for marks so nobody did them.
